From: Barry <barry@curran.co>
Date: 2026-05-14
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] EFMesh: default owner short_name + long_name

Bakes the EFMesh ambassador owner identity into the firmware at compile
time via userPrefs.jsonc:

  long_name  = "Join 100+ EFMesh.com on MediumFast!"   (35 utf-8 bytes,
               fits in char long_name[40] with null terminator)
  short_name = "⚠"  (U+26A0, 3 utf-8 bytes, fits in char short_name[5]
               with null terminator)

NOTE on short_name: the original request was "⚠️" (warning sign +
variation selector U+FE0F, 6 utf-8 bytes). That does NOT fit in the
5-byte protobuf short_name field. We strip the variation selector. On
the Heltec V3/V4 1-bit monochrome OLED, the variation selector has no
effect anyway — the device renders the bare ⚠ glyph from its built-in
font. The phone-app node list also displays the bare warning sign.

The actual edit lives in this repo at src/userPrefs.jsonc. Drop that
file at the root of a clean upstream Meshtastic firmware checkout
(replacing the upstream userPrefs.jsonc) before building.

Effective diff applied:

--- a/userPrefs.jsonc
+++ b/userPrefs.jsonc
@@ -25,8 +25,12 @@
   // "USERPREFS_CONFIG_LORA_REGION": "meshtastic_Config_LoRaConfig_RegionCode_US",
-  // "USERPREFS_CONFIG_OWNER_LONG_NAME": "My Long Name",
-  // "USERPREFS_CONFIG_OWNER_SHORT_NAME": "MLN",
+  // "USERPREFS_CONFIG_OWNER_LONG_NAME": "My Long Name",
+  // "USERPREFS_CONFIG_OWNER_SHORT_NAME": "MLN",
+  // ---- EFMesh ambassador defaults ----
+  "USERPREFS_CONFIG_OWNER_LONG_NAME": "Join 100+ EFMesh.com on MediumFast!",
+  "USERPREFS_CONFIG_OWNER_SHORT_NAME": "⚠",
   // "USERPREFS_CONFIG_DEVICE_ROLE": "meshtastic_Config_DeviceConfig_Role_CLIENT",
